solutions.content:
**Idea:-**
1. Iterate over ```grid``` and find the start position and count the umber of empty cells(including start position,that's why i initilized empty with 1).
2. Now start backtrackin  from start posiiton and mark visited to every empty cells(by assigning it ```-2``` or other different value) and also decrease ```empty```.
3. When we complete backtracking from current cell then restore the previous values(empty++,grid[row][col]=0). 
4. When we reach ```end``` position our ```empty``` variable should be ```0``` because we have to count number of paths that include every ```empty cell.```.

**Time Complexity:-** ```O(3^(m*n))```,where m,n are row,columns of grid.
4th one is not included because we can't go back to same posiiton.
**Space Complexity:-** ```O(1)```, I am not using stack space as i am passing by ```reference```.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int uniquePathsIII(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
       int m=grid.size(),n=grid[0].size(),ans=0,startRow,startCol,empty=1;
        for(int i=0;i<m;i++)
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                if(grid[i][j]==1){
                    startRow=i; startCol=j;
                }
                else if(grid[i][j]==0)
                    empty++;
            }
        helper(grid,startRow,startCol,ans,m,n,empty);
          return ans;          
    }
    void helper(vector<vector<int>>& grid,int &row,int&col,int &ans,int &m,int &n,int &empty){
        if(row<0 || row>=m || col<0 || col>=n || grid[row][col]==-1 || grid[row][col]==-2)
            return;
        if(grid[row][col]==2){
            if(empty==0)
              ans++;
            return;
        }
        grid[row][col]=-2;  empty--;
        vector<vector<int>>dirs={{1,0},{0,1},{-1,0},{0,-1}};
        for(auto & i:dirs){
            row+=i[0];   col+=i[1];
            helper(grid,row,col,ans,m,n,empty);
            row-=i[0];  col-=i[1];
        }
        grid[row][col]=0; empty++;
    }
};
```
