class Solution {
    public int uniquePathsIII(int[][] A) {
		int i = 0, j = 0, n = A.length, m = A[0].length;
		int p = 0, q = 0, zero = 0;
		for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
			for (j = 0; j < m; j++) {
				if (A[i][j] == 1) {
					p = i;
					q = j;
				}
				if (A[i][j] == 0)
					zero += 1;
			}
		}
		//p and q are starting position
		int totalPath = getPathCount(p, q, A, zero, 0);
		return totalPath;
	}

	private int getPathCount(int x, int y, int[][] path, int zero, int cnt) {
	   // If any of this condition is true we will not be having any path. (checking for out of bound and          obstacle)
		if (x < 0 || y < 0 || x == path.length || y == path[0].length || path[x][y] == -1) {
			return 0;
		}
		if (path[x][y] == 2) {
		    // Found path, then check for total non-obstacle .
			if (cnt == zero + 1) {
				return 1;
			}
			return 0;
		}
		path[x][y] = -1;  // making this grid as obstacle to avoid looping in same path 
		cnt += 1;  
		int d1 = getPathCount(x + 1, y, path, zero, cnt);
		int d2 = getPathCount(x - 1, y, path, zero, cnt);
		int d3 = getPathCount(x, y + 1, path, zero, cnt);
		int d4 = getPathCount(x, y - 1, path, zero, cnt);
		path[x][y] = 0;  // re-setting path as non-obstacle.
		return d1 + d2 + d3 + d4;

	}
}
```
**Time Complexity:**
Since for every sqaure we are traversing in 4 direction and we can have (N*M)-2  sqaure with 0 (in worst case).
TC: O(4^NM) 

**Space Complexity:**
SC: O(NM)

