Create a dictionary of key => List of (timestamp, value)
For e.g: "foo" => [(1,"bar"), (5,"bar2")]

"constantly increasing" property of timestamps makes insertion in "set" operation easy by just appending the values in the list. 

As the list is sorted, use binary search to get the value in O(logn) time. 
Time taken for get: O(1) to find the key, O(logn) to get the value => O(logn)
Time taken for set: O(1) for insertion in a list

