# :)
**Time Complexity :**
* set() => O(1) ,  values can be inserted in unordered_map in O(1) time. + also, values can be appended in vector in O(1) time.
* get() => O(logn),  using binary-search to search for the timestamp in map[vector] which is equal to given targetted timestamp or just less than that.

**Space Complexity :**
* O(n) : for storing all given data in unordered_map.

```
class TimeMap {
public:
		unordered_map<string, vector<pair<int,string>> > mp;  // mp[key] = {[timestamp, value]};

