**Idea:** Use a hashmap of key to a sorted map, of timestamp to value, to store the values in ascending order of timestamps
>T/S: O(m lg m)/O(m), where m = size(timemap)
>*constructor:* O(1)/O(1)
>*set:* O(lg n)/O(1), where n = size of timemap at this call
>*get:* O(lg n)/O(1)
```
class TimeMap {

	private final Map<String, TreeMap<Integer, String>> timemap = new HashMap<>();

	/**
	 * Initializes the object of the data structure.
	 */
	public TimeMap() {}

	/**
	 * Stores the key = key with the value = value at the given time timestamp.
	 */
	public void set(String key, String value, int timestamp) {
		timemap.computeIfAbsent(key, k -> new TreeMap<>())
			   .put(timestamp, value);
	}

	/**
	 * @return a value such that set was called previously, with timestamp_prev <= timestamp.
	 * If there are multiple such values, it returns the value associated with the largest timestamp_prev.
	 * If there are no values, it returns ""
	 */
	public String get(String key, int timestamp) {
		return timemap.containsKey(key) && timemap.get(key).floorEntry(timestamp) != null 
			 ? timemap.get(key).floorEntry(timestamp).getValue() 
			 : "";
	}
}
```
