we're iterating over all the values from 0 to 216-1 for each A[i]. But we can make this loop faster by skipping over numbers that we can be sure wouldn't give 0 when taken AND with A[i]. Let's say, a (from A) = xxxx1000 and i (from loop) = 1000 so that a & i = 00001000 which is != 0. At this point, we can be sure that subsequent values after i i.e. 1001, 1010, 1011, 1100, ..., 1111 when taken AND with a won't give 0 either because all of these have a 1 at bit position 3 so we can directly skip ahead to i = 10000. Note that this is essentially the same as previous approach in spirit.

