# Approach
-> Seeing the constraints, we know that n^2 solution will pass. 
-> So, we first store the frequency of every (a[i]&a[j]) pair we can get inside an unordered_map.
-> Then we need to find the kth index, for which we again iterate through the array and check for every index.
-> Finally, if the condition is satisified we add it to the answer.

# Code
```
class Solution 
{
public:
    int countTriplets(vector<int>& nums) 
    {
        unordered_map <int,int> mp;
        for(auto x:nums)
        {
            for(auto y:nums)
            {
                mp[(x&y)]++;
            }
        }
        int ans=0;
        for(auto x:mp)
        {
            for(auto y:nums)
            {
                if((x.first&y)==0)
                ans+=x.second;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

