# Approach
First calculate bitwise AND of every pair of array and store the frequency of that result in a vector. Now iterate the given array once again and do bitwise AND of every element with every index of previously calculated vector. If the result is 0 then add the frequency of the index to the answer.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n*n + n*(pow(2,16)))$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(pow(2,16))$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int countTriplets(vector<int>& nums) {
        int ans=0;
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<int> tmp(pow(2,16)+1);
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
            {
                tmp[nums[i]&nums[j]]++;
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<tmp.size();i++)
        {
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
            {
                if((i&nums[j])==0)
                ans+=tmp[i];
            }
        }
        return ans;

    }
};
```

