solutions.content:
Solution works well, but times seem a bit sluggish - any inputs would be appreciated.

Solved this problem in two rounds.

* Round 1 - checked all possible combinations of A. Counted how many times each result was reached and remembered new results

* Round 2 - checked all combinations of A v.s. the results of round 1. Each time zero was reached,  the number of times the first number was reached in round 1 was added to final result.

Check it out: 

```
class Solution {
public:
    int countTriplets(vector<int>& A) {

        int ans = 0; 
        int n = A.size();
        set<int> round1Results;
        vector<int> round1Histogram(pow(2,16));

		//round 1
        //first the diagonal
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int res = A[i];
            round1Results.insert(res);
            round1Histogram[res]++;
        }

        //next the top half
        for (int i=0; i< n; i++ ) {
            for (int j=i+1; j< n; j++) {
                int res = A[i] & A[j];
                round1Results.insert(res);
                round1Histogram[res]+=2;
            }
        }

        //round 2
        //we compare the results of round 1 with A and try to reach zero
        for (int i=0; i< n; i++) {
            for (int res1 : round1Results ) {
                if ((res1 & A[i]) == 0) {
                    ans+= round1Histogram[res1];
                }
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```

